msgstr "Compared to a conventional fast filter, the FRAMCA:"

#: ../../Filtration/Filt_Purpose_and_Description.rst:33
msgid "No requiere de bombas para el retrolavado."
msgstr "It does not require pumps for backwashing."

#: ../../Filtration/Filt_Purpose_and_Description.rst:34
msgid "Ocupa seis veces menos área para tratar el mismo caudal."
msgstr "It takes up six times less area to treat the same flow."

#: ../../Filtration/Filt_Purpose_and_Description.rst:35
msgid "Gasta menos agua para el retrolavado."
msgstr "It uses less water for backwashing."

#: ../../Filtration/Filt_Purpose_and_Description.rst:36
msgid ""
"Se retrolava con agua sedimentada, no con agua filtrada. De esta manera se "
"puede usar la misma agua que está entrando al filtro para retrolavarlo. No "
"hay necesidad de tanques adicionales para almacenar agua filtrada."
msgstr ""
"It is backwashed with sedimentary water, not filtered water. This way you "
"can use the same water that is entering the filter to backwash it. There is "
"no need for additional tanks to store filtered water."

#: ../../Filtration/Filt_Purpose_and_Description.rst:37
msgid ""
"Ingresa y egresa el agua a través de manifolds dentro del lecho de arena."
msgstr "Water enters and exits through manifolds into the sand bed."

#: ../../Filtration/Filt_Purpose_and_Description.rst:38
msgid "Filtra el agua por una capa de arena más delgada."
msgstr "It filters the water through a thinner layer of sand."

#: ../../Filtration/Filt_Purpose_and_Description.rst:46
msgid ""
"El FRAMCA, por su configuración en seis capas, logra los mismos resultados "
"como seis filtros convencionales."
msgstr ""
"The FRAMCA, because of its six-layer configuration, achieves the same "
"results as six conventional filters."

#: ../../Filtration/Filt_Purpose_and_Description.rst:54
msgid ""
"El FRAMCA de AguaClara en los dos modos principales de operación: el ciclo "
"de filtración y el ciclo de retrolavado."
msgstr ""
"The FRAMCA of AguaClara in the two main modes of operation: the filtration "
"cycle and the backwash cycle."

